Module A — Functional Group Alert.

Molecule:
- Canonical SMILES: {{ smiles }}
{% if iupac %}- IUPAC: {{ iupac }}{% endif %}

RDKit inventory (use as a guide, NOT as a ceiling):
- Hazard-tagged SMARTS hits: {{ detected_groups | tojson }}
- Full fragment counts (rdkit.Chem.Fragments fr_*): {{ fragments | tojson }}

Task:
Produce a COMPREHENSIVE list of functional groups present in this molecule, then
judge each one's practical risk under common bench conditions (thermal stability,
shock sensitivity, genotoxicity, biological reactivity, storage hazards).

Important:
- Do NOT limit yourself to the inventory above. If you can identify a group from
  the SMILES/IUPAC that the inventory missed (e.g. specific heterocycles, ether
  subtypes, stereochemistry-sensitive motifs), include it.
- For ANY group you list that is not obviously in the inventory above, you MUST
  provide a SMARTS pattern (`smarts` field) so RDKit can verify your claim. If
  the group is clearly in the inventory, `smarts` may be omitted.
- Mark severity honestly — most common groups are "low".

Return JSON ONLY:
{
  "alerts": [
    {
      "group": "<name, lowercase, underscore-separated>",
      "severity": "low" | "medium" | "high",
      "risk": "<one-sentence rationale>",
      "smarts": "<SMARTS pattern; required when group is NOT in the inventory>",
      "self_confidence": <float 0..1>
    }
  ],
  "overall_self_confidence": <float 0..1>
}
